\title{Cartesian Product}
\taxon{Definition}

\p{The cartesian product is a binary operation defined between two sets, that produces a set of all ordered pairs from the arguments.}
##{\set{a,b,c,...}\times\set{\alpha,\beta,\gamma,...}=\Set{(a,\alpha),(a,\beta),(a,\gamma),...,(b,\alpha),(b,\beta),(b,\gamma),...}}
\p{or}
##{A\times B=\set{All\; ordered\; pairs\; of A\;and\;B}}
\p{Note: Since the cartesian product is a set, we are not limited to only creating binary operations. We can go to arbitrarily higher orders.}
##{A\times B\times C\times D}